:1,"options":["Patient rude and unreasonable, raised voice because of wait time","Patient expressed dissatisfaction regarding wait time","Patient raised voice when discussing wait time","Patient appeared agitated during discussion about waiting","Patient concerns about wait time documented and addressed"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe inappropriate documentation is \u003Cstrong\u003EPatient rude and unreasonable, raised voice because of wait time\u003C/strong\u003E. This entry contains subjective judgments (\u0027rude and unreasonable\u0027) which are unprofessional and potentially legally problematic. Medical documentation should be objective and avoid personal opinions about patient behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe appropriate documentation options are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient expressed dissatisfaction regarding wait time\u003C/strong\u003E - Objective and factual description\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient raised voice when discussing wait time\u003C/strong\u003E - Describes specific behaviour without judgment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient appeared agitated during discussion about waiting\u003C/strong\u003E - Observational and professional\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPatient concerns about wait time documented and addressed\u003C/strong\u003E - Professional and solution-focused\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical records are legal documents that should be objective, factual, and professional. They should describe behaviours and events without including personal judgments or derogatory comments. This ensures respect for patient dignity while still accurately documenting relevant clinical interactions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical records must be accurate, up-to-date, legible, and comprehensible to other healthcare practitioners.","Medical records should be objective and professional, avoiding subjective or derogatory comments about patients.","Patient confidentiality requires secure storage and protection of medical records from unauthorised access."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76192"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18838"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76192"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-19T16:13:18+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-19T16:13:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11571"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92827"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinic